news.title: Dehradun: Illegal construction of Rs 9 crore at Lansdowne forest division
news.para: The team’s report, exclusively accessed by TOI, reveals that construction work was being carried out without the MoEF’s nod at an eco-park spread across 0.5 hectares of land in the forest division.

news.title: Uphaar fire tragedy: Delhi court awards seven-year jail to Sushil & Gopal Ansal
news.para: The court also awarded 7-year-jail term each to former court staff Dinesh Chand Sharma and two others -- P P Batra and Anoop Singh and a fine of Rs 3 lakh each on the them.

news.title: Kotak Mahindra Bank hikes home loan rates by 0.05%
news.para: The private sector lender will now be offering home loans starting from 6.55 per cent, as against 6.50 per cent earlier, as per an official statement.

news.title: Housing finance companies to grow at 8-10% in FY22: Report
news.para: Its vice president and sector head (financial sector ratings) Sachin Sachdeva said the overall on-book portfolio of HFCs in India is estimated at Rs 11 lakh crore as of June 30, 2021, with exposures across home loans (HLs), loan against property (LAP), construction finance (CF), and lease rental discounting (LRD).

news.title: Gaurs Group trims debt by 35% to Rs 1,550 crore
news.para: Gaurs Group has a receivables of around Rs 2,000 crore from customers against the properties already sold, while the pending construction cost is estimated at only Rs 400 crore.

news.title: Sobha posts net profit of Rs 48.3 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: The board has approved the issue of unlisted secured non-convertible redeemable debentures (NCDs) on a private placement basis. The size of the issue is Rs 140 crore in one or more tranches, Sobha said in the regulatory filing.

news.title: Ludhiana: F&CC likely to discuss civic body taking over Glada colonies on Nov 8
news.para: For almost four years, officials were sitting over this proposal to take over 16 colonies and urban schemes which at present are being managed by Glada.

news.title: Rajasthan government mulls relief for colonies in smaller cities sans zonal plans
news.para: The state government was aiming to issue 10 lakh lease deeds during the campaign. The major attraction of the campaign was regularisation of colonies on agricultural land.

news.title: Pune civic body's 50-year-old quarters in Parvati area up for redevelopment
news.para: Tenders worth Rs 13 crore have been approved. Though the project has been cleared, a group of residents are opposing the construction.

news.title: Punjab cabinet approves reduction in interest on enhancement from allottees
news.para: ​The rate of interest to be charged on the enhancement recoverable will be reduced from 15 per cent to 7.5 per cent. This decision was taken in the cabinet meeting chaired by Chief Minister Charanjit Singh.

news.title: Rajasthan: 1.29 lakh PMAY-Gramin houses incomplete, officials to face action
news.para: Also, all the districts have been directed to complete construction of the remaining houses by December 31, 2021, stated the letter written to the districts by rural development department secretary Krishna Kant Pathak.

news.title: Rajasthan RERA disposed of 90% complaints from home buyers this year
news.para: This state is at the third position in the country to resolve the problems of the home-buyers. An official said, "The Rajasthan RERA received 1,484 complaints till Diwali, which were redressed by the authority."

news.title: Experion to invest $300 million in student housing
news.para: “We plan to open our first property in the next academic year, which will begin in June 2022,” said BK Malagi, CEO and board member of Experion Developers. “We’ll go with an asset-heavy approach in which we own and operate the property.”

news.title: Mumbai: 100-year-old chawl will make way for 36-storey tower
news.para: The state’s housing authority, Mhada, gave the go-ahead on October 27 to redevelop Old Chikhalwadi at Tardeo. The 1.54-acre plot comprising a labyrinth of 12 chawls, in which over 200 people live, stands behind Bhatia Hospital.

news.title: Gurugram: DHBVN issues notices to eight builders over failure to develop power infra
news.para: The Dakshin Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam (DHBVN) has recently issued notices to all the defaulters, giving them two-week time to take corrective steps for developing the required infra.
